Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: MCC cell lines were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% FBS and antibiotics.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The ChIP method was modified from protocols described in Schmidt et al.(Schmidt et al., 2009). MKL-1 cells were cross-linked using dual cross-linking with disuccinimidyl glutarate (DSG) and formaldehyde. After cross-linking, cells were lysed using SimpleChIP buffer A and B (Cell signaling) and DNA was processed with the Micrococcal nuclease (New England Biolabs Inc.) for 30 minutes at 37°C followed by sonicating for 20s pulses 5 times at 4°C., 30 ng of DNA from ChIP experiments or input DNA were prepared for sequencing with NEBNext ChIP-seq Library Prep Reagent Set for Illumina (New England BioLabs). Amplified libraries were cleaned up using AMPure XP beads (Beckman Coulter) and checked on a Bioanalyzer (Agilent) to confirm a narrow distribution with a peak size around 275 bp. Diluted libraries were used for 50 cycles single-end sequencing on NextSeq 550 systems  (Illumina) at the Molecular Biology Core Facilities (MBCF) at Dana-Farber Cancer Institute following the manufacturer’s protocol.
Sample_data_processing: ChIP-seq reads were aligned to the hg19 genome assembly using the BWA aligner, peaks were called using using the default parameters of MACS2 relative to the input samples.
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: .narrwPeak.bed and .xls peak files were generated using MACS2.

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: MCC cell lines were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% FBS and antibiotics.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: RNA libraries were prepared for sequencing using TruSeq Stranded mRNA library prep kit
Sample_data_processing: The Illumina NextSeq500 was used to generate reads., STAR was used to map reads to the hg19 genome and reads were  aligned using samtools., The count (TPM) files were generated using the htset-count function.
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Cells were treated with either GSK-LSD1 or CPI-670242 for 1 or 3 days and harvested for RNA using Qiagen Rneasy plus kit

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: MCC cell lines were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% FBS and antibiotics.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: The ChIP method was modified from protocols described in Schmidt et al.(Schmidt et al., 2009). MKL-1 cells were cross-linked using dual cross-linking with disuccinimidyl glutarate (DSG) and formaldehyde. After cross-linking, cells were lysed using SimpleChIP buffer A and B (Cell signaling) and DNA was processed with the Micrococcal nuclease (New England Biolabs Inc.) for 30 minutes at 37°C followed by sonicating for 20s pulses 5 times at 4°C., 30 ng of DNA from ChIP experiments or input DNA were prepared for sequencing with NEBNext ChIP-seq Library Prep Reagent Set for Illumina (New England BioLabs). Amplified libraries were cleaned up using AMPure XP beads (Beckman Coulter) and checked on a Bioanalyzer (Agilent) to confirm a narrow distribution with a peak size around 275 bp. Diluted libraries were used for 50 cycles single-end sequencing on NextSeq 550 systems  (Illumina) at the Molecular Biology Core Facilities (MBCF) at Dana-Farber Cancer Institute following the manufacturer’s protocol.
Sample_data_processing: ChIP-seq reads were aligned to the hg19 genome assembly using the BWA aligner, peaks were called using using the default parameters of MACS2 relative to the input samples.
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: .narrwPeak.bed and .xls peak files were generated using MACS2.

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: MCC cell lines were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% FBS and antibiotics.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Cells were washed with PBS twice to achieve >85% viable cells in pellets. ATAC-seq protocol was modified from Corces et al., The transpose reaction was performed using TDE1 Tn5 transposase (15027865; Illumina) and TD buffer (15027866; Illumina). The reactions were cleaned up using MinElute PCR Purification Kit (28004; Qiagen) and amplified using NEBNext High-Fidelity 2X PCR Master Mix (M0541S; New England Biolabs Inc.) with a total of 7 cycles. The libraries were cleaned up using MinElute PCR Purification Kit and additionally with AMPure XP beads (Beckman Coulter) to remove primer dimers and large fragments.
Sample_data_processing: For analysis, the adapters were removed using NGmerge and the reads were mapped to hg38 reference using Bowtie2 and sorted by SAMtools., peaks were called using using the default parameters of MACS2 relative to the input samples., ATAC-seq peaks were merged, annotated, and visualized using the BEDtools and the ChIPseeker, ChIPpeakAnno, and DiffBind R packages and Integrative genome viewer (IGV; Broad Institute)
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Two independent replicates of 70,000 MKL-1 MCC cells were harvested for ATAC-seq after treatment with GSK-LSD1 0.1µM, dBRD9 0.1µM, or both for three days.
